## 5. ΣCard — Stream Registration

Every source that publishes to the bus must register a ΣCard before its first message.
The MatrixRegistry rejects messages from unregistered sources in strict mode.

### 5.1 ΣCard Schema

```json
{
  "card_id": "string (uuid-v4)",
  "path": "string (fully-qualified path)",
  "schema_id": "string (schema name + version)",
  "registered_by": "string (agent UID)",
  "registered_at_us": "integer (unix microseconds)",

  "what": {
    "data_type": "float64 | float32 | int32 | uint16 | uint8 | string | bool | compound",
    "unit": "string (SI unit or 'none')",
    "valid_range": [null, null],
    "modality": "sensor | derived | agent | command | desktop | rf | transaction"
  },

  "where": {
    "source_id": "string",
    "source_type": "hardware | software | agent | external",
    "interface": "nmea0183 | nmea2000 | signalk | can | serial | sdr | screenshot | api"
  },

  "when": {
    "update_rate_hz": "number",
    "max_age_ms": "number",
    "half_life_s": "number",
    "timestamp_resolution": "us | ms | s"
  },

  "trust": {
    "trust_class": "hardware | calculated | inferred | external | command",
    "base_trust": "number (0.0–1.0)",
    "cross_validators": ["list of sibling paths that validate this one"]
  },

  "access": {
    "consumer_acl": ["list of agent UIDs or * for unrestricted"],
    "producer_acl": ["list of agent UIDs allowed to write"]
  },

  "retention": {
    "class": "ephemeral | realtime | voyage | permanent",
    "archive_priority": "integer (1=always, 10=drop first)"
  }
}
```

### 5.2 Trust Classes

| Class | Base Trust | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `hardware` | 0.95–1.00 | Direct physical sensor reading, calibrated hardware |
| `calculated` | 0.70–0.95 | Derived from hardware via deterministic formula (Kalman, CPA) |
| `inferred` | 0.40–0.70 | Agent-generated inference — always flagged as such |
| `external` | 0.50–0.80 | Data received from external system (AIS, weather API) |
| `command` | N/A | Write-only path — trust applies to issuing agent, not value |

### 5.3 Half-Life Reference Table

| Data Type | Half-Life | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| GPS position | 2 s | Vessel moves; stale position is wrong position |
| Speed over ground | 5 s | Inertia — changes more slowly |
| AIS target position | 10 s | Remote vessel; update rate limited by AIS itself |
| AIS target CPA/TCPA | 5 s | Derived, depends on own position staleness |
| Engine RPM | 3 s | Mechanical; fast-changing |
| Engine temperature | 30 s | Thermal mass; slow-changing |
| Battery voltage | 10 s | Moderate change rate |
| Battery SoC | 60 s | Integrated quantity; slow |
| Weather forecast | 21600 s | 6 hours |
| Agent decision | 30 s | Reasoning validity window |
| Desktop UI state | 0.5 s | Screen changes rapidly |
| SDR burst event | 1 s | Transient RF event |
| Chart data | ∞ | Edition-stamped; expires on edition change only |

