## 6. ΣFrame — The Message Unit

Every message on the bus is a ΣFrame. A ΣFrame is a typed payload plus a SemanticEnvelope.

### 6.1 Wire Format

```json
{
  "msg_id":       "string (uuid-v4)",
  "msg_type":     "string (see §6.2)",
  "sender":       "string (agent UID)",
  "subject":      "string (fully-qualified path)",
  "timestamp_us": "integer (unix microseconds at time of creation)",
  "schema_id":    "string (payload schema name + version)",
  "payload":      "object (typed per schema_id)",
  "envelope":     "SemanticEnvelope (see §7)",
  "signature":    "string (base64:ed25519-signature)"
}
```

### 6.2 Message Type Vocabulary

The `msg_type` field classifies the intent of the frame. CM-level message types (ANNOUNCE,
PROPOSE, etc.) are defined in `SIGMABUS-CM-SPEC.md`. Core data types are:

| Type | Direction | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `OBSERVATION` | Source → Bus | Raw or derived sensor reading |
| `COMMAND` | Agent → Actuator | Write instruction to a controlled system |
| `EVENT` | Any → Bus | Discrete occurrence (alarm triggered, waypoint reached) |
| `HEARTBEAT` | Agent → Bus | Liveness signal (see CM spec) |
| `SCHEMA_ANNOUNCE` | Registry → Bus | New path registered on the bus |
| `HEALTH_REPORT` | Registry → Bus | Periodic system health summary |

### 6.3 Constraints

- `msg_id` must be globally unique. Use UUIDv4.
- `timestamp_us` must be set at **origin**, not at relay. Never overwrite.
- `payload` must validate against the schema identified in `schema_id`.
- `signature` must cover the canonical JSON of all fields except `signature` itself (fields sorted, no whitespace).
- Maximum frame size: **1 MB**. Frames exceeding this are rejected at the transport layer.

