## 7. SemanticEnvelope — Metadata Plane

The SemanticEnvelope is the load-bearing metadata layer. It travels with every ΣFrame.
It is never stripped in transit. Consumers may cache it separately for performance.

```json
{
  "identity_trust":    "float (0.0–1.0) — PKI verification score of sender",
  "behavioral_trust":  "float (0.0–1.0) — rolling Brier-scored outcome history",
  "evidence_trust":    "float (0.0–1.0) — provenance chain quality of this message",
  "authority_scope":   ["list of path prefixes this sender may write"],

  "half_life_s":       "float — data type half-life in seconds",
  "t_origin_us":       "integer — when the physical event occurred (if known)",
  "t_sensed_us":       "integer — when the sensor measured it",
  "t_encoded_us":      "integer — when it was serialised into the frame",
  "t_expires_us":      "integer or null — null = never expires",

  "path":              ["ordered list of nodes this frame passed through"],
  "derived_from":      ["list of msg_ids this frame was derived from"],
  "data_class":        "sensor | derived | inferred | command | negotiation",
  "cross_validated":   "bool",
  "validators":        ["list of source_ids that cross-validated this value"],
  "anomaly_score":     "float (0.0–1.0) — 0=normal, 1=extreme anomaly",

  "priority":          "integer (1=critical, 10=background)",
  "retention":         "ephemeral | realtime | voyage | permanent",
  "consumer_acl":      ["list of agent UIDs or * for unrestricted"],

  "annotations":       "object — agent-written shadow stream (see §7.1)"
}
```

### 7.1 Shadow Annotations

Agents may attach annotations to any ΣFrame they process. These are written to
the `annotations` field and do not modify the primary payload. This is the NTFS
Alternate Data Streams pattern applied to the message bus.

```json
"annotations": {
  "nav_agent": {
    "agent_confidence": 0.94,
    "cross_check_delta_kn": 0.1,
    "historical_mean_kn": 6.1,
    "anomaly_note": null,
    "t_annotated_us": 1716123456892000
  }
}
```

### 7.2 Effective Trust Computation

```
effective_trust(T) = base_trust × (0.5) ^ (delta_t_s / half_life_s)

where:
  base_trust  = trust_class baseline adjusted for anomaly_score and cross_validation
  delta_t_s   = (now_us - t_origin_us) / 1_000_000
  half_life_s = from ΣCard registration
```

This is computed by consumers at read time, not stored in the envelope. The envelope
carries the parameters needed to compute it, not a pre-computed value that would
immediately go stale.

### 7.3 Anomaly Score Influence on Trust

```
base_trust_adjusted = base_trust
                    - (anomaly_score × 0.5)
                    + (0.10 if cross_validated else 0.0)
                    - min(age_penalty, 0.30)

where age_penalty = delta_t_s / (10 × half_life_s)
```

