## 8. ΣTags Reference

ΣTags are structured metadata attached to the envelope. They are named, typed, and their
vocabulary is controlled by this specification.

| Tag | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `trust_class` | enum | From ΣCard registration |
| `novelty_score` | float | How different this reading is from recent history (0=routine, 1=unprecedented) |
| `anomaly_score` | float | Statistical anomaly vs calibrated distribution |
| `policy` | string | Applicable policy identifier (e.g., `colreg_rule_16`) |
| `retention` | enum | Storage retention class |
| `focus_window` | string | For desktop streams: active window name |
| `display_server` | string | For desktop streams: `windows` \| `x11` \| `wayland` |
| `compositor` | string | For Wayland: `gnome` \| `kde` \| `wlroots` |
| `sdr_channel` | integer | For RF streams: SDR channel index |
| `sdr_freq_hz` | integer | For RF streams: centre frequency |
| `sigMF_ref` | string | For RF streams: path to SigMF metadata file |
| `scenario` | string | Operational scenario tag (e.g., `colreg_encounter`, `anchoring`) |

