## 11. MatrixBus

The MatrixBus is the routing and validation layer. Every message that flows in the system
passes through it.

### 11.1 Publish Pipeline

```
receive ΣFrame
    │
    ├─► [1] Signature verification (Ed25519)
    │        REJECT if invalid → log security_event
    │
    ├─► [2] Path lookup in MatrixRegistry
    │        REJECT if unknown and strict_mode=True
    │
    ├─► [3] Producer ACL check
    │        REJECT if sender not in card.producer_acl
    │
    ├─► [4] Schema validation
    │        REJECT if payload does not conform to schema_id
    │
    ├─► [5] Envelope validation
    │        REJECT if required fields missing or trust < 0.0
    │
    ├─► [6] Size check (max 1MB)
    │        REJECT if frame > MAX_PAYLOAD_BYTES
    │
    ├─► [7] Update MatrixRegistry (last_seen, current_value)
    │
    ├─► [8] CEP pattern matching
    │        Fire registered patterns against new value
    │
    └─► [9] Notify subscribers (filtered by consumer_acl)
```

### 11.2 CEP Pattern Registration

Agents may register Complex Event Processing patterns that fire callbacks when stream
values meet conditions. This is the primary mechanism for keeping the agent tier shielded
from raw stream volume.

```python
class CEPPattern:
    path:       str          # stream path to watch
    condition:  Callable     # (value, envelope) → bool
    callback:   Callable     # async (matched_frame) → None
    priority:   int          # 1=critical, fires first
    ttl_s:      float | None # auto-expire pattern after this duration
```

