## 12. Trust Decay Model

### 12.1 Formula

```
effective_trust(t) = base_trust_adjusted × (0.5) ^ (delta_t_s / half_life_s)

base_trust_adjusted = base_trust
                    - (anomaly_score × 0.50)
                    + (0.10 if cross_validated else 0.0)
                    - min(delta_t_s / (10 × half_life_s), 0.30)
```

### 12.2 Trust Floor

```
effective_trust(t) ≥ 0.0    (never negative)
effective_trust(t) ≤ 1.0    (capped at registration base)
```

### 12.3 Trust Propagation Rules

When a derived value is computed from source values, its trust is bounded by its inputs:

```
derived_trust = min(source_trust_values) × derivation_fidelity_factor

derivation_fidelity_factor:
  Kalman filter:    0.95
  Linear interp:    0.90
  Statistical est:  0.75
  LLM inference:    0.60  (always flagged data_class: "inferred")
```

