## 13. Retention Classes

| Class | Duration | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `ephemeral` | seconds | Never persisted. Lost on restart. UI states, transient RF. |
| `realtime` | minutes | Kept in memory only. Lost on restart. Engine telemetry during passage. |
| `voyage` | voyage duration | Persisted to voyage log. Cleared on departure of new voyage. |
| `permanent` | indefinite | Never deleted without explicit operator instruction. Alarms, decisions, events. |

---

## 14. Stream Health Model

The MatrixRegistry publishes a health summary at configurable intervals (default: 10 seconds)
to `{platform}.meta.stream.health`.

```json
{
  "schema_id":   "meta.health_report.v1",
  "timestamp_us": 1716123456000000,
  "summary": {
    "total":    42,
    "nominal":  38,
    "degraded":  3,
    "absent":    1
  },
  "degraded_paths": ["wibo835.comms.hf.js8call.last_rx"],
  "absent_paths":   ["wibo835.engine.port.fuel_rate"]
}
```

Agents should subscribe to this path and escalate to the human operator when
`absent_paths` includes safety-critical streams (nav, engine alarms, power).

